   "source": [
    "## Summary & Usage\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides a complete pipeline for parsing hierarchical section text and building a temporary parent-child tree in memory.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Components:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Section Parser** - Detects numbering patterns (1., 2.1., 3.1.1., etc.) and extracts hierarchy levels\n",
    "2. **Hierarchy Builder** - Constructs an in-memory tree linking parents to children\n",
    "3. **Parent-Child Notation** - Generates a normalized representation with full relationship info\n",
    "4. **Tree Renderer** - Displays the hierarchy with indentation and visual markers\n",
    "5. **Validation Engine** - Checks for structural issues and inconsistencies\n",
    "6. **Query Interface** - Search and navigate the temporary hierarchy\n",
    "\n",
    "### Output Formats:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Tree View**: Indented ASCII tree with visual connectors\n",
    "- **Tabular View**: DataFrame showing parent-child relationships\n",
    "- **Structured Data**: Dictionary-based notation with complete metadata\n",
    "- **Query Results**: Flexible search across the temporary data structure\n",
    "\n",
    "### No Database Required:\n",
    "\n",
    "All data structures are stored temporarily in notebook variables:\n",
    "- `sections` - List of Section objects\n",
    "- `hierarchy` - Dict with sections lookup and root_ids\n",
    "- `notation_data` - List of parent-child notation entries\n",
    "- `validation_results` - Validation report dictionary\n",
    "- `df` - Pandas DataFrame for tabular display\n",
    "\n",
    "Simply re-run the notebook to process new input text!"
   ]
  },
